commitResults.messageTitle: Fix internship .equals() to check equality for all data fields

commitResults.messageBody:
The contains method for UniqueInternshipList is used to check
for unique internships. Internship has some identity fields,
namely companyName, location, role and description.

Currently, the .contains() method actually uses the stronger
definition of equality defined in Internship, which checks for
the equality of all data fields.

Let's change .contains() to use .isSameInternship() in Internship
that only checks for equality for the identity fields.

commitResults.messageTitle: Set result display box to wrap result text
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently the text overflows and expands the text area, so
the user is unable to see the full error/result message
unless he scrolls to the right with a mouse.

In light of efficiency purposes, it is better to have the text
wrap around the text area so it will not extend horizontally
past the border.

Let's set the wrap text property to true for better user QOL.

commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, when an internship is being edited, if it is being
displayed on the detailed view window, it would dissapear on occasion.
This is discovered to be because the identity fields of Internship
are being used to check for equality (aka isSameInternship()).

It would be useful for users if the internship that is being viewed
does not dissapear upon any field update.

This is made possible with a simple change to edit command. By
checking if the internship to be edited is the model's current
selected internship (which is the one displayed in the GUI), the
post-edit internship can be set to the new selected internship
in model. (A non selected internship post-edit will NOT appear
in the detailed view window).

This is corroborated by 2 additional test cases in
InternshipEditCommandTest which checks that a selected internship
post edit will still be the selected internship, and a non-selected
internship will not become the selected internship.

Let's implement these changes within edit command.

commitResults.messageBody:
Our current implement of model that sets the predicate to
show all internships upon execution of most commands causes
the find filter to be reset every time a command is executed.

There are a few exceptions like delete, sort etc. that are also
highlighted in this change.

Let's

For future reference

commitResults.messageTitle: Increase visibility of caution message for copy pasting commands
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, there is a warning to users about copy pasting commands
directly from the PDF version of the UG under the 'Notes about
command format' section.

This is not very visible to users as it is the 4th bullet point
and is likely to be skipped through.

Let's
* Improve it's visibility by wrapping in a 'Caution' formatting
* Place it at the beginning in 2 places, under `Tutorial` and
`Commands` sections since these are the places where the user
is most likely to copy paste commands.
